    • Enum Constant Detail

      • NOT

        public static final SentenceImpl.SentenceOperatorImpl NOT
        Return a new sentence with sent sentence wrapped with #$not. #$not in queries requires that a sentence be provably false. Therefore in queries it is generally more useful to specify #$unknownSentence for the sub-sentence that is required to be not-provable. Use UNKNOWN for that.

      • UNKNOWN

        public static final SentenceImpl.SentenceOperatorImpl UNKNOWN
        Return a new sentence with sent sentence wrapped with #$unknownSentence. If this type of sentence is part of a query sentence, the query will only be provable if this sentence is not provable in the context.

      • ASSERTED

        public static final SentenceImpl.SentenceOperatorImpl ASSERTED
        Return a new sentence with sent sentence wrapped with #$assertedSentence. If this type of sentence is part of a query sentence, Cyc will return true only if this sentence is explicitly asserted in the KB, not just inferrible.

      • CHECK

        public static final SentenceImpl.SentenceOperatorImpl CHECK
        Return a new sentence with sent sentence wrapped with #$checkSentence. If this type of sentence is part of a query, Cyc will ensure that this sentence is considered for solving only when all the open variables are bound, by solving other clauses of the query first.
